&lt;p&gt;Gittins index is generally difficult to calculate. For a more elaborate formulation of the Gittins index, see the paper &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.ece.mcgill.ca/~amahaj1/projects/bandits/book/2013-bandit-computations.pdf&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Multi-Armed Bandits, Gittins Index, and It’s Calculation&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; by Jhelum Chakravorty and Aditya Mahajan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;resources&#34;&gt;Resources&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.ece.mcgill.ca/~amahaj1/projects/bandits/book/2013-bandit-computations.pdf&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Multi-Armed Bandits, Gittins Index, and It’s Calculation by Jhelum Chakravorty and Aditya Mahajan&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;footnotes&#34;&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li id=&#34;fn1&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Algorithms to Live By&lt;/em&gt; by Brian Christian and Tom Griffiths - Explore/Exploit&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fnref1&#34;&gt;↩︎&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li id=&#34;fn2&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Geometric discounting&lt;/em&gt; refers to each decision to explore is worth a constant fraction of the last one.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fnref2&#34;&gt;↩︎&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content><link href="https://marklucernas.dev/the-gittins-index"/></entry></feed>